(119, 0, 126, 4, 'on', 2, '2', 'a:7:{s:5:"title";s:35:"World News: Tensions With Iran Rise";s:7:"content";s:9337:"<p><span style=\\"font-size: small;\\"><strong>World News:</strong></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\\"font-size: medium;\\"><strong>Tensions&nbsp;With Iran Rise</strong></span></p>\r\n<p>Written by Cheyenne Williams</p>\r\n<p><img title=\\"Mahmoud Ahmadinejad\\" src=\\"http://a57.foxnews.com/images/309170/450/350/0_21_ahmadinejad_mahmoud_111406.jpg\\" alt=\\"Mahmoud Ahmadinejad\\" width=\\"241\\" height=\\"169\\" /><img title=\\"Strait of Hormuz Map\\" src=\\"http://www.toledoblade.com/image/2011/12/28/800x_b1_cCM_z/strait-of-hormuz-map.jpg\\" alt=\\"Strait of Hormuz Map\\" width=\\"273\\" height=\\"169\\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\\"text-align: left;\\"><span style=\\"font-family: times new roman,times; font-size: small;\\"><em>Courtesy of <a href=\\"http://a57.foxnews.com/images/309170/450/350/0_21_ahmadinejad_mahmoud_111406.jpg\\">Fox News</a> and <a href=\\"http://www.toledoblade.com/image/2011/12/28/800x_b1_cCM_z/strait-of-hormuz-map.jpg\\">ToledoBlade</a></em></span></p>\r\n<p style=\\"text-align: left;\\"><span style=\\"font-size: small;\\">Lately, America&rsquo;s and Israel&rsquo;s situation with Iran has heated considerably during the latter months of last year and has since continued to grow in intensity.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\\"font-size: small;\\">Although a combination of events led to the ultimate upheaval of aggression towards Iran, the underlying driving force behind all of this concern is Iran&rsquo;s developing nuclear program. Iran continues to claim that the program is meant to be used for peaceful purposes, such as generating electrical power, but time and again the country&rsquo;s top leaders have vowed to use nuclear missiles for&nbsp;radical Islamist&nbsp;ambitions &ndash; in particular, to incinerate Israel. Back in October 2005, the Iranian President Mahmoud Ahmadinejad&rsquo;s speech transcript directed toward the &ldquo;World Without Zionism&rdquo; conference in Asia (his contribution to a conference with that name alone blatantly shows the Iranian President&rsquo;s hostility towards Jewish people) was posted in the New York Times. A quote expressing his opinion over the Israel-Palestinian territory issue was translated as this:</span></p>\r\n<p style=\\"padding-left: 30px;\\"><span style=\\"font-size: small;\\">\\"Our dear Imam (referring to Ayatollah Khomeini, the Supreme Leader of Iran from 1979-89) said that the occupying regime (referring to Israel) must be wiped off the map and this was a very wise statement. We cannot compromise over the issue of Palestine . . . This would be a defeat and whoever accepts the legitimacy of this regime has in fact, signed the defeat of the Islamic world. Our dear Imam targeted the heart of the world oppressor in his struggle, meaning the occupying regime. I have no doubt that the new wave that has started in Palestine, and we witness it in the Islamic world too, will eliminate this disgraceful stain from the Islamic world.\\"</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\\"font-size: small;\\">This was not the only time Ahmadinejad, as well as other Iranian leaders, revealed their genocidal intent towards Israel. More threats stated by Ahmadinejad are listed with precise references on <a href=\\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mahmoud_Ahmadinejad_and_Israel#Statement_on_9.2F11_attacks\\">Wikipedia</a>.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\\"font-size: small;\\">The threats to wipe Israel off the map and the growing nuclear&nbsp;capability to make that come true are the foremost factors in shaking relations with Iran to fragility. Although the United States under this administration has not taken any stronger steps as of yet than imposing oil sanctions on Iran along with the European Union (rendered ineffective by China&rsquo;s, Russia&rsquo;s, and India&rsquo;s refusal to join in on the embargo because of the profitable market that comes from selling weapons to Iran and not taking the threat of Iran seriously), Israel&rsquo;s national security precautions cannot afford to take the back seat, as shown by a series of sabotage plots employed over the past few years.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\\"font-size: small;\\">Just last month, a key Iranian nuclear scientist was killed with a magnetic car bomb in Tehran, marking him the fourth Iranian scientist death in two years. Other implements, such as computer viruses, have also been applied to curb Iran&rsquo;s nuclear development. The United States and Britain denied any involvement with the attacks, and Israeli spokesmen refused to comment on the subject, but it is most likely that it was Israel&rsquo;s intelligence organizations that have been carrying out these assassinations. The U.S.&rsquo;s CIA has similar apparatuses and security motives for such operations and therefore could have had&nbsp;a hand in some of the plots as well.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\\"font-size: small;\\">Iran has responded to these plots with their recent contentious decisions. In December last year, a U.S. drone &ndash; the RQ-170 Sentinel &ndash; malfunctioned and crashed into Iran. It was retrieved by Iranian officials and displayed on their television channels nearly intact. Rather than implement any operations to destroy the aircraft, the administration resorted to asking Iran to please return the drone &ndash; a request Iran&nbsp;sneered at. Worries amount that although Iran with its relatively primitive technology would not extract much from the drone, they could still sell it to Russia or China, either of which would be able to make better use of the potential intelligence and engineering secrets behind the drone. To push the envelope further, Iran demanded an apology from the United States for &lsquo;invading&rsquo; their airfield.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\\"font-size: small;\\">About two weeks after this incident, a report came out about the finalization of America&rsquo;s sale of F-15SA fighting jets to Saudi Arabia, a nearby Middle Eastern country that serves for now as an ally to the United States. Saudi Arabia and Iran are currently local rivals, and stiffness between them rose higher after the attempted assassination of the Saudi ambassador to the United States on American soil earlier last year, which is believed to be plotted by Iranian officials. Although there were concerns that giving Saudi Arabia such weaponry would undermine Israel&rsquo;s military edge, it was still given the go-ahead on the account that Iran poses the greater danger to America&rsquo;s and Israel&rsquo;s national security.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\\"font-size: small;\\">The implementation of the oil sanctions still continues today. In response to the embargo a month earlier, Iran threatened to&nbsp;target&nbsp;Western ships passing&nbsp;through the Strait of Hormuz, which is an important waterway for oil trade. The Iranian Parliament introduced a bill that would require foreign ships to be granted permission from Tehran to enter and leave the Strait. Several U.S. Navy ships moved closer to the waterway in retaliation&nbsp;to the threat, and declared that any blockage placed by Iran in this waterway would be deemed an act of war. </span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\\"font-size: small;\\">Despite all of this conflict, America still holds virtue above hate. Just days after Iran\\''s threatening of&nbsp;a Navy aircraft carrier against&nbsp;reentering the Strait of Hormuz, that same carrier rescued 13 Iranian sailors from pirates that held their ship hostage for over a month. The Iranian foreign ministry responded by upholding this as a \\"humanitarian and positive act.\\"</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\\"font-size: small;\\">Nevertheless, Iran still holds its world domination and terrorist ambitions, so the international&nbsp;tension with Iran remains far from dying down for a while yet.</span></p>\r\n<p><strong><span style=\\"font-size: small;\\">Sources:</span></strong></p>\r\n<p><strong></strong><span style=\\"font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: small;\\">U.S. Rescue of Iranian Sailors:&nbsp;<a href=\\"http://www.foxnews.com/world/2012/01/07/iran-hails-us-rescue-sailors-as-humanitarian-and-positive-act/\\" target=\\"_blank\\">http://www.foxnews.com/world/2012/01/07/iran-hails-us-rescue-sailors-as-humanitarian-and-positive-act/</a></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\\"font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: small;\\">Europeans Plan Oil Embargo On Iran: <a href=\\"http://online.wsj.com/article/SB10001424052970203471004577140583587139896.html?mod=WSJ_article_comments#articleTabs%3Darticle\\" target=\\"_blank\\">http://online.wsj.com/article/SB10001424052970203471004577140583587139896.html?mod=WSJ_article_comments#articleTabs%3Darticle</a></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\\"font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: small;\\">U.S. Finalizes Sale of F-15s to Saudi Arabia: <a href=\\"http://www.foxnews.com/politics/2011/12/29/us-to-sell-f-15s-to-saudi-arabia-officials-say/?intcmp=trending\\" target=\\"_blank\\">http://www.foxnews.com/politics/2011/12/29/us-to-sell-f-15s-to-saudi-arabia-officials-say/?intcmp=trending</a></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\\"font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: small;\\">Request for Return of Drone: <a href=\\"http://www.foxnews.com/politics/2011/12/13/us-formally-requests-drone-return-iran-scoffs/\\" target=\\"_blank\\">http://www.foxnews.com/politics/2011/12/13/us-formally-requests-drone-return-iran-scoffs/</a></span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>";s:8:"comments";s:1:"0";s:7:"message";s:0:"";s:4:"user";s:3:"274";s:4:"time";i:1329185650;s:7:"changes";s:1:"1";}', '', '', '', 'a:7:{s:5:"title";s:35:"World News: Tensions With Iran Rise";s:7:"content";s:9337:"<p><span style=\\"font-size: small;\\"><strong>World News:</strong></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\\"font-size: medium;\\"><strong>Tensions&nbsp;With Iran Rise</strong></span></p>\r\n<p>Written by Cheyenn