pan style=\\"font-family: Calibri; font-size: small;\\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; In Ireland, St. Patrick&rsquo;s Day is a religious holiday and the celebrations start with Mass in the morning. St. Patrick&rsquo;s Day is during the season of Lent, and this season used to require Catholics to abstain from meat all through Lent instead of just on Fridays and Ash Wednesday. On this holiday, Catholics were allowed to eat meat and they celebrated with traditional Irish dishes, such as Irish bacon and cabbage. Before the 1970s, Irish pubs were closed on St. Patrick&rsquo;s Day, but now they remain open and Ireland uses this holiday to increase tourism.&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\\"font-family: Calibri; font-size: small;\\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\\"font-family: Calibri; font-size: small;\\">Sources: </span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\\"font-family: Calibri; font-size: small;\\">http://www.catholic.org/saints/saint.php?saint_id=89</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\\"font-family: Calibri; font-size: small;\\">http://www.history.com/topics/st-patricks-day&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\\"font-family: Calibri;\\">&nbsp;</span></p>";s:8:"comments";s:1:"1";s:7:"message";s:0:"";s:4:"user";s:3:"248";s:4:"time";i:1335227386;s:7:"changes";s:1:"0";}', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
