rbid-snowmen/</a></p>\r\n<p>Once again I chose a Calvin and Hobbes cartoon, yet this one is very different from the last one, even though it involves snowmen. His parents seem to not appreciate Calvin&rsquo;s creativity because it passes the wrong message about their child. Calvin has a knack for creating funny situations involving snowmen like the one above. Calvin structured the snowmen so that the one &ldquo;supposedly&rdquo; hit by the car and is looked at by the three other snowmen. His father though, used to Calvin&rsquo;s foolish snow scapes, groans and wonders why Calvin makes his life so hard. The cartoon can be interpreted in many ways, people can think that its Calvin&rsquo;s parents that fail to embrace Calvin&rsquo;s creativity or it can be though of Calvin just being bored and wanting to annoy his parents. Anyway or the other the cartoon remains funny!</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Videogame Recommendation</strong>: <a href=\\"http://www.andkon.com/arcade/puzzle/flashchess3/\\">http://www.andkon.com/arcade/puzzle/flashchess3/</a></p>\r\n<p>Name: Flash Chess III</p>\r\n<p>Type: Strategy</p>\r\n<p>Levels: Three: Advanced, Casual and Novice.</p>\r\n<p>Summary: Match your wits against the computer and see if you can beat it! Chess is a very old game and has been around for a while, so I thought why not try an older, more classical game this time.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Music Recommendation/ Commemoration.</strong></p>\r\n<p><em>Type: Rock</em></p>\r\n<p><em>Artist: Led Zeppelin</em></p>\r\n<p><em>Song: Moby Dick</em></p>\r\n<p><span style=\\"text-decoration: underline;\\">Summary:</span> This song is a great song for both rock lovers and the casual listener.It has a great beat and is interesting to listen to with the different tone. It is a pleasant and upbeat song, something that is always nice to listen to.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Monthly Recipe:</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong><span style=\\"text-decoration: underline;\\">Up for a Fruity taste? &ndash; Toast Hawaii</span></strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>&nbsp;<img src=\\"http://bellmagazine.co.cc/files/Screen%20shot%202012-03-15%20at%206.37.13%20PM.png\\" alt=\\"\\" width=\\"429\\" height=\\"493\\" /></strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Ingredients:</strong></p>\r\n<p>Italian Bread, Toasted for two minutes.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Ham, 12 slices</p>\r\n<p>Pineapple, canned or fresh, also 12 slices</p>\r\n<p>Swiss Cheese, 12 slices</p>\r\n<p>Place the toast on a tray and start stacking the ham, then the pineapple, four slices per toast. Then add the cheese. Put the tray under the broiler and wait until the cheese has browned, this process takes about 8 &ndash; 12 minutes. After the time has past, enjoy your meal!</p>";s:8:"comments";s:1:"0";s:7:"message";s:0:"";s:4:"user";s:3:"248";s:4:"time";i:1335227376;s:7:"changes";s:1:"0";}', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(123, 0, 70, 1, 'on', 2, '3', 'a:7:{s:5:"title";s:27:"Philadelphia Warehouse Fire";s:7:"content";s:3031:"<p><img style=\\"float: left;\\" src=\\"http://i.i.com.com/cnwk.1d/i/tim/2012/04/09/philadelphia_fire_AP1204090_620x350.jpg\\" alt=\\"\\" width=\\"366\\" height=\\"187\\" />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <span style=\\"color: #c0c0c0; font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: x-small;\\">By GIANNA TORRES </span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<span style=\\"color: #c0c0c0;\\">Published: April 17, 2012</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\\"font-family: times new roman,times; font-size: small;\\">Two Philadelphia firefighters were laid to rest last week due a massive fire at an abandoned warehouse. The massive fire was in Kensington section of Philadelphia that went on for two hours until being brought under control. This happened on the day of April 9, 2012 at 3:15 in the morning. The fire went on for hours, and thankfully nobody was in the warehouse that was seriously injured. But two Philadelphia firefighters were injured, and two were killed in the raging fire. </span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\\"font-family: times new roman,times; font-size: small;\\"><span style=\\"color: #c0c0c0;\\"><em>*Courtesy of <a href=\\"http://www.cbsnews.com\\"><span style=\\"color: #c0c0c0;\\">www.cbsnews.com</span></a></em></span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\\"font-family: times new roman,times; font-size: small;\\">The firefighters that were injured were sent to Temple University Hospital. The two Philadelphia firefighters that lost their lives were Lt. Robert P. Neary, 60, and Daniel Sweeney, 25. Each of them loved their </span><span style=\\"font-family: times new roman,times; font-size: small;\\">job and were decorated many times for rescuing people from burning buildings. Neary was four years away from retirement and Sweeney was five years into his career. The last time Ladder 10 lost multiple firemen was in 2004. There was recently a benefit for the families that lost their loved ones and raised was more than $7,000. However there was a theif that took items donated to the families and that person is still on the loose. Just recently it has been announced that the grand jury will investigate this warehouse fire that claimed the lives of two Philadelphia firefighters to find out if something went wrong or if there is somebody to blame.</span></p>\r\n<pre style=\\"color: #000000; text-transform: none; line-height: normal; text-indent: 0px; letter-spacing: normal; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; word-spacing: 0px; orphans: 2; widows: 2; background-color: #ffffff; -webkit-text-size-adjust: auto; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;\\">&nbsp;</pre>";s:8:"comments";s:1:"1";s:7:"message";s:0:"";s:4:"user";s:3:"271";s:4:"time";i:1334687800;s:7:"changes";s:1:"1";}', 'a:2:{i:0;s:5:"Emily";i:1;s:13:"Matthew Brown";}', 'a:2:{i:0;i:1337002686;i:1;i:1337191013;}', 'a:2:{i:0;s:361:"<p>That is so devistating that someone would steal the donations. Seriously, where is the common sence. I give prayers to those whom lost their loved ones in the fire. Thank You Firefighters!!</p>\r\n<p>I am very <span style=\\"text-decoration: line-through;\\">appriciative </span>thankful for those firefighters that risk their lives everytime a fire happens.</p>";i:1;s:98:"<p>It\\''s nice to know that nice people are out there when there is an emergencie, like a fire.</p>";}', 'a:7:{s:5:"title";s:27:"Philadelphia Warehouse Fire";s:7:"content";s:3031:"<p><img style=\\"float: left;\\" src=